<item>
            <title>[CXF-4341] AccessTokenService does not identify the authentication scheme</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-4341</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Inside AccessTokenService when checking if the client is authenticated (method authenticateClientIfNeeded), the condition to find out the authentication scheme used by an already authenticated client compares to &quot;Basic&quot; and a value as &quot;BASIC&quot; evaluates it to false.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In my environment (tomcat 7 + jdk 1.6 + CXF 2.6.1 last snapshot), after SSL activation and added the following security constraint to oauth2 endpoint: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &amp;lt;security-constraint&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;web-resource-collection&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;web-resource-name&amp;gt;OAuth Services&amp;lt;/web-resource-name&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;url-pattern&amp;gt;/services/oauth2/token&amp;lt;/url-pattern&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/web-resource-collection&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;auth-constraint&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;role-name&amp;gt;OAUTH2_USER&amp;lt;/role-name&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/auth-constraint&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;/security-constraint&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;login-config&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;auth-method&amp;gt;BASIC&amp;lt;/auth-method&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;realm-name&amp;gt;OAuth services&amp;lt;/realm-name&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;/login-config&amp;gt;  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SecurityContext.getAuthenticationScheme() always returns &quot;BASIC&quot;. Wouldn&apos;t be better to ignore upper/lower case?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
